    "raw": "ALTERNATIVE (minimal) design. Original todo: 557ab9d3. Full cascade counterpart:\nALT:complete, todo 2493fb7d (2493fb7de5f3d5b6a8570e8213ba05734f39e62f536b4dc6649f10ce1098909d).\n\nScope: static routing only -- no orchestrator, no gate/escalation, no episodic memory.\n\n- Add optional enum fields to a WorkItem/subtodo execution block:\n    execution.capability: haiku | sonnet | opus | fable\n    execution.effort: low | medium | high | xhigh | max\n  Both optional; absent means inherit current defaults (behavior unchanged).\n- Groomed during the frequentcommits sizing pass, where difficulty is already assessed.\n- Dispatch passes them through verbatim: Agent(model=...) or Workflow agent(prompt,\n  {model, effort}) -- same dispatch-table pattern as execution.primitive.\n- doctor accepts the fields as optional enums; no new hard findings.\n- work-item-read next hint surfaces them when present.\n\nForward-compatible: these fields are the router half of the cascade in ALT:complete\n(2493fb7d); nothing here is discarded if the complete design lands later.\n\nSEED WORKITEMS -- promote to real WorkItems at init (tool gap: set-json-path\ncannot write WorkItems on a branchless pre-init todo):\n\n1. [task] Devise, in consultation with the user (do not decide unilaterally), a\n   way to populate the suggested execution.capability/execution.effort fields\n   based on the todo Body and existing WorkItems upon entering state init. The\n   population itself should be done by a high-capability agent. Open question is\n   how to invoke it: part of the todos skill (user wants to avoid re-entrancy:\n   agent -> todo -> agent), or a gate on starting to work the todo -- if fields\n   are not populated, fire up a hicap agent to fill them in as an implicit first\n   work-item."
  },
